==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nepotism
<hw>Nep"o*tism</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nepus</ets>, <ets>nepotus</ets>, nephew: cf. F.
<ets>n⟦eacute⟧potisme</ets>. See <er>Nephew</er>.]</ety> <def>Undue
attachment to relations; favoritism shown to members of one's family;
bestowal of patronage in consideration of relationship, rather than of
merit or of legal claim.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From <qex>nepotism</qex> <person>Alexander V.</person> was safe;
for he was without kindred or relatives. But there was another perhaps
more fatal <qex>nepotism</qex>, which turned the tide of popularity
against him -- the <qex>nepotism</qex> of his order.</q>
<rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nepotist</ent>⟦br⟧
